Course Summary

This Saxon Algebra 2 Textbook Companion Course uses interesting videos to help students learn algebra and earn a better grade. The lessons are about five minutes long and are sequenced to align with the chapters in the Saxon Algebra 2 textbook.

Who's It For?

Anyone enrolled in a class using the Saxon Algebra 2 textbook should consider this companion course. You will learn the material faster, retain it longer and earn a better grade.

How It Works

  • Identify the chapter in your Saxon Algebra 2 textbook with which you need help.
  • Find the corresponding chapter within our Saxon Algebra 2 Textbook Companion Course.
  • Watch fun videos that cover the algebra 2 topics you need to learn or review.
  • Complete the quizzes to test your understanding.
  • If you need additional help, re-watch the videos until you've mastered the material or submit a question for one of our instructors.

Why It Works

  • Fun Content: These videos make learning Saxon Algebra 2 fun with engaging animation and real-world examples.
  • Great Instructors: Study.com uses exceptional educators who can take concepts like graphing linear equations and make them easy to understand.
  • Multiple Ways to Learn: Watch videos or read the lesson transcript.
  • Easy to Use: Access this textbook companion on any smartphone, tablet or laptop.

Students will learn topics including:

  • Decimals
  • Graphing on the coordinate plane
  • Set notation
  • Real and complex numbers
  • Converting numbers
  • Ratios, proportions, percents and rates
  • Exponents
  • Roots, probability and statistics
  • Simplifying and solving expressions
  • Linear and quadratic equations
  • Trigonometry and functions
  • Lines, planes and angles
  • Shapes
  • Perimeter, circumference and area
  • The Pythagorean Theorem
  • Geometric proofs
